# COALITION STABILITY TRACKING
# ============================================

@coalition_stability_check
title: Coalition Stability
view-if: num_partners >= 3
on-arrival: {!
    Q.partners_list = Q.government_parties.join(', ');
    Q.num_partners = Q.government_parties.length;
!}

**Current Coalition:** [+ coalition_name +]

**Partners:** [+ partners_list +]

**Reichstag Support:** [+ coalition_votes +]%

**Coalition Dissent:** [+ coalition_dissent +]

[? if coalition_dissent >= 1 : The coalition is showing signs of strain. ?]

[? if coalition_dissent >= 2 : The coalition is in serious trouble. A vote of no confidence may be imminent. ?]

[? if kpd_in_government : **KPD Coalition Dissent:** [+ kpd_coalition_dissent +] ?]

[? if kpd_coalition_dissent >= 2 : The KPD is threatening to withdraw from the coalition. ?]

































// ============================================
// MINISTRY RENEGOTIATION SCENE
// ============================================

@ministry_renegotiation
title: Ministry Reshuffle
subtitle: Reallocate cabinet positions within the current coalition

**Current Coalition:** [+ government_coalition_type +]

**Current Ministry Allocation:**

[+ ministry_display_list +]

The current distribution reflects the balance of power when the coalition was formed. We can attempt to renegotiate ministry positions, but this may strain coalition relations.

- @begin_ministry_shuffle: Begin ministry shuffle
- @cancel_shuffle: Keep current arrangement

@begin_ministry_shuffle
on-arrival: {!
// Store original allocation for comparison
Q.original_allocation = {
    foreign: Q.foreign_minister_party,
    interior: Q.interior_minister_party,
    justice: Q.justice_minister_party,
    labor: Q.labor_minister_party,
    economic: Q.economic_minister_party,
    finance: Q.finance_minister_party,
    agriculture: Q.agriculture_minister_party,
    transport: Q.transport_minister_party
};

// Calculate current leverage (may have changed since coalition formation)
var coalition = Q.government_parties;
var total_coalition_votes = 0;

for (var i = 0; i < coalition.length; i++) {
    var party = coalition[i];
    var party_lower = party.toLowerCase();
    total_coalition_votes += Q[party_lower + '_r'];
}

// GUARD AGAINST ZERO
if (total_coalition_votes === 0 || isNaN(total_coalition_votes)) {
    total_coalition_votes = 1;
}

Q.shuffle_leverage = {};

for (var i = 0; i < coalition.length; i++) {
    var party = coalition[i];
    var party_lower = party.toLowerCase();
    
    var base = (Q[party_lower + '_r'] / total_coalition_votes) * 100;
    
    var relation_var = party_lower + '_relation';
    var relation = Q[relation_var] || 50;
    base += (relation - 50) / 5;
    
    if (Q.chancellor_party === party) {
        base += 10;
    }
    
    // SPD-specific bonuses
    if (party === 'SPD') {
        if (Q.president === 'Braun') base += 5;
        if (Q.spd_prussia) base += 3;
        if (Q.coalition_dissent > 3) base -= 5;
    }
    
    Q.shuffle_leverage[party] = Math.max(base, 5);
}

// ============================================
// DEDUCT LEVERAGE FOR MINISTRIES ALREADY HELD
// ============================================

var ministry_costs = {
    labor: 5,
    interior: 10,
    justice: 10,
    finance: 15,
    economic: 15,
    foreign: 15,
    agriculture: 10,
    transport: 8,
    reichswehr: 20
};

for (var ministry in ministry_costs) {
    if (!ministry_costs.hasOwnProperty(ministry)) continue;
    
    var party_var = ministry + '_minister_party';
    var holding_party = Q[party_var];
    
    if (holding_party && Q.shuffle_leverage[holding_party] !== undefined) {
        Q.shuffle_leverage[holding_party] -= ministry_costs[ministry];
    }
}

// Floor at 0
for (var party in Q.shuffle_leverage) {
    if (!Q.shuffle_leverage.hasOwnProperty(party)) continue;
    Q.shuffle_leverage[party] = Math.max(0, Q.shuffle_leverage[party]);
}

Q.shuffle_spd_variable = Q.shuffle_leverage.SPD || 0;

// Convert to display format
Q.shuffle_leverage_display = "";
for (var party in Q.shuffle_leverage) {
    if (!Q.shuffle_leverage.hasOwnProperty(party)) continue;
    var rounded = Math.round(Q.shuffle_leverage[party] * 10) / 10;
    Q.shuffle_leverage_display += "- **" + party + "**: " + rounded + " leverage\n";
}
!}

**Updated Leverage:**

[+ shuffle_leverage_display +]

- @ministry_picker: Proceed with reshuffle
- @cancel_shuffle: Cancel

@ministry_picker
tags: ministry_shuffle_root

We can now attempt to claim or drop ministries. Each change costs or returns leverage based on ministry importance.

**Current SPD Ministries:**
[? if labor_minister_party = "SPD" : Labor (cost: 5) ?]
[? if interior_minister_party = "SPD" : Interior (cost: 10) ?]
[? if justice_minister_party = "SPD" : Justice (cost: 10) ?]
[? if finance_minister_party = "SPD" : Finance (cost: 15) ?]
[? if economic_minister_party = "SPD" : Economic (cost: 15) ?]
[? if foreign_minister_party = "SPD" : Foreign (cost: 15) ?]
[? if agriculture_minister_party = "SPD" : Agriculture (cost: 10) ?]
[? if transport_minister_party = "SPD" : Transport (cost: 8) ?]
[? if reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD" : Reichswehr (cost: 20) ?]

**Available Leverage:** [+ shuffle_spd_variable +]

- @claim_labor: Claim Labor Ministry (cost: 5)
- @claim_interior: Claim Interior Ministry (cost: 10)
- @claim_justice: Claim Justice Ministry (cost: 10)
- @claim_finance: Claim Finance Ministry (cost: 15)
- @claim_economic: Claim Economic Ministry (cost: 15)
- @claim_foreign: Claim Foreign Ministry (cost: 15)
- @claim_agriculture: Claim Agriculture Ministry (cost: 10)
- @claim_transport: Claim Transport Ministry (cost: 8)
- @claim_reichswehr: Claim Reichswehr Ministry (cost: 20)
- @drop_labor: Drop Labor Ministry (gain: 5)
- @drop_interior: Drop Interior Ministry (gain: 10)
- @drop_justice: Drop Justice Ministry (gain: 10)
- @drop_finance: Drop Finance Ministry (gain: 15)
- @drop_economic: Drop Economic Ministry (gain: 15)
- @drop_foreign: Drop Foreign Ministry (gain: 15)
- @drop_agriculture: Drop Agriculture Ministry (gain: 10)
- @drop_transport: Drop Transport Ministry (gain: 8)
- @drop_reichswehr: Drop Reichswehr Ministry (gain: 20)
- @finalize_shuffle: Finalize reshuffle

@claim_labor
title: Claim Labor Ministry
unavailable-subtitle: [? if labor_minister_party = "SPD" : Already controlled ?][? if shuffle_spd_variable < 5 : Not enough leverage ?]
choose-if: labor_minister_party != "SPD" and shuffle_spd_variable >= 5
on-arrival: {!
    Q.shuffle_leverage.SPD -= 5;
    Q.shuffle_spd_variable = Q.shuffle_leverage.SPD;
    Q.previous_labor_party = Q.labor_minister_party;
    Q.labor_minister_party = "SPD";
    Q.labor_minister = "Wissell";
    
    if (Q.previous_labor_party && Q.previous_labor_party !== 'I') {
        var rel_var = Q.previous_labor_party.toLowerCase() + '_relation';
        Q[rel_var] = Math.max(0, (Q[rel_var] || 50) - 5);
    }
!}
